-- Saskatchewan-BHP Billiton Talks Over Potash Break Down, NYT Says
-- B y   C h r i s   P e t e r s o n
-- 2010-10-21T06:01:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-21/saskatchewan-bhp-billiton-talks-over-potash-break-down-nyt-says.html
Talks between the government of
Saskatchewan and BHP Billiton Ltd. over the Australian miner’s
$40 billion hostile bid for Potash Corp. of Saskatchewan Inc.
have broken down, the New York Times reported, citing a person
familiar with the matter.  The two sides failed to agree on how much BHP would pay
into a special infrastructure fund for the Canadian province,
which is now expected to formally oppose the deal today if the
question of lost tax revenue isn’t addressed, the newspaper
said, citing the person familiar  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Chris Peterson at 
 cpeterson@bloomberg.net  